**Most critical gap**: `red-cell-c2-i9b2` — `handle_config_callback` has 12 DemonConfigKey variants but only WorkingHours is tested. Two variants (`KillDate` and `WorkingHours`) mutate agent state and persist to the database; a regression in any of the other 10 would produce wrong operator console messages with no test to catch it.

**Overall test quality**: The `dispatch/` module has impressively deep coverage in `dispatch/mod.rs` (6,693 lines of tests). `events.rs` is well-tested. The gaps are mostly uncovered branches within already-tested handlers (error class variants, job subcommands) rather than entire functions without any tests. The codebase shows mature testing discipline.
